entry.tran: （用作从句中动词或代词的宾语，指代动词主语“我”或“任何人”）自己，自身
entry.def: A speaker or writer uses oneself as the object of a verb or preposition in a clause where 'oneself' meaning 'me' or 'any person in general' refers to the same person as the subject of the verb.

example.ex: One must apply oneself to the present and keep one's eyes firmly fixed on one's future goals...
example.tran: 人们必须立足现在，目光锁定未来目标。

example.ex: To work one must have time to oneself.
example.tran: 一个人要工作就必须有属于自己的时间。

entry.tran: （one 虽缺失但可理解为动词主语时，用作动词或介词的宾语）自己，自身
entry.def: Oneself can be used as the object of a verb or preposition, when 'one' is not present but is understood to be the subject of the verb.

example.ex: The historic feeling of the town makes it a pleasant place to base oneself for summer vacations...
example.tran: 该镇的历史气息让它成为人们夏季度假的好去处。

example.ex: The only guarantee of having a cabin to oneself is by travelling first class...
example.tran: 只有坐头等舱旅行才能保证一个人独享一舱。

entry.def: To do something oneself means to do it without any help from anyone else.

example.ex: It is a very rewarding exercise to work this out oneself...
example.tran: 独自解决这个问题是一次受益匪浅的锻炼。

example.ex: Some things one must do oneself.
example.tran: 有些事情必须亲自去做。

entry.tran: （强调事情发生的对象）自己，自身
entry.def: You use oneself to emphasize that something happens to you rather than to people in general.

example.ex: It is better to die oneself than to kill.
